data.title: Croatia - Population 2023
data.meta_description: Croatia ended 2023 with a population of 3,861,967 people, which represents an increasea of 11,073 people compared to 2022.
data.text:
Croatia ended 2023 with a population of 3,861,967 people, which represents an increasea of 11,073 people compared to 2022.

Croatia ranks No. 130 among196 countries which published this information in countryeconomy.com.

The female population is greater, with 1,989,028 women, representing 51.65% of the total, compared to 1,861,866 or 48.35% men.

Croatia shows a moderate population density, with 44 people per square km and it was in position 57th in our ranking of density population in 2023.
